gomodel:SYNGO_2923  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"USP46 deubiquitinates glutamate receptor subunit 1 (GluA1) in vivo and in vitro\"\n\nFig.5: \"Knockdown of USP46 reduces both surface and total AMPARs in hippocampal neurons\"\n\nFig.6: \"Over-expression of USP46 increases surface AMPAR expression\"\n\nFig.7: \"Effect of USP46 on AMPAR internalization\"\n\nFig.8: \"USP46 regulates AMPAR mediated synaptic currents\"\n\nNotes:\n- The authors remark that \"Ubiquitinated surface AMPARs are marked for efficient endocytosis, leading to inhibited synaptic transmission (Lin et al. 2011).\"\n- In Fig.6 the authors show \"We found that the surface GluA1 was significantly enhanced by USP46 over-expression. Quantification indicated a significant difference between EGFP control and cells with USP46 over-expression (Fig. 6a and b) (EGFP: 1 ± 0.05, n = 9 cells; USP46: 1.20 ± 0.05, n = 10 cells, p = 0.002). In contrast, no significant changes were detected in total GluA1 in neurons expressing either USP46 or USP12 (Fig. 6c and d) (EGFP: 1.0 ± 0.07, n = 9 cells; USP46: 1.08 ± 0.09, n = 9 cells, p = 0.20).\" This argues for a role of USP46 in regulation of AMPAR endocytosis and not in protein degradation. I have refrained from making the annotation to term 'regulation of protein catabolic process at postsynapse, modulating synaptic transmission (GO:0099576)' because not sufficiently supported by the data.. Experimental description: - \"Primary cultured cortical and hippocampal neurons were prepared from embryonic day 18 rat embryos as previously described (Hou et al. 2008).\"\n- \"Cortical tissue dissected from adult rat brains was ....\"\n- Over-expressed USP46 was of rat species: \"Full length rat USP46 and USP12 were PCR amplified t...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2923" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

